<bdy>

The <b>Linde-Buzo-Gray algorithm</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../805/47805.xml">
vector quantization</link> algorithm to derive a good <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../786/530786.xml">
codebook</link>.
It is similar to the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../407/1860407.xml">
k-means</link> method in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../675/669675.xml">
data clustering</link>.
<sec>
<st>
The algorithm </st>
<p>

At each iteration, each vector is split into two new vectors.</p>
